Durban- DA leader in KwaZulu-Natal Zwakele Mncwango is to due to hand over a dossier to the Hawks detailing alleged instances of corruption in the eThekwini Municipality.

 Mncwango revealed this on Monday following a meeting he held with the head of the Hawks in the province General Jabulani Zikhali.

The dossier will include some of the forensic reports that have been leaked to the media and opposition parties by whistleblowers. Most of these forensic reports were a product of investigations launched to probe the awarding of various tenders, some of which were found to be irregular.













